working on a branch:

main_user   = LeonardoESousa
repo_name   = KMC
branch_name = dev

git clone git@github.com:main_user/repo_name
cd repo_name/
git remote -v
git remote add main_user  git://github.com/main_user/repo_name
git fetch origin
git checkout -b dev origin/branch_name

to add changes:
git add . (or git add -A)
git commit -m "some text"
git push origin branch_name


Someonelse did changes:
git pull main_user master
git push


How to update fork after BIG changes in main:
On your fork page (https://github.com/TSA-Cassiano/KMC) click fetch upstream
git checkout -b LeonardoESousa-main main
git pull git@github.com:LeonardoESousa/KMC.git main

Modify the files manually to allow the merging

git add .
git commit -m "Resolvendo merging"
git checkout main
git merge --no-ff LeonardoESousa-main
git push origin main
